    <note type="biography">
        <p>Lawyer. Second son of Erasmus Darwin (1731–1802) and his first wife, Mary. CD’s uncle. Wished to retire at the age of 40. Purchased Breadsall Priory. Drowned in the river at the bottom of his garden; his death was thought to be suicide by many family members, including CD.</p></note>
